title: For Sale:  Nazi RZM-Marked Walther PPK .32, Mfg. 1935Another Collectible Handgun From Jackson Armory
postcontent: RZM-Marked Walther PPK, Mfg. 1935, Nazi Party Pistol. Stock # MSH250803SP. Serial # 898xxx. One of over a thousand Antique and Modern Collectible firearms, including Military, Sporting, Custom and Tactical guns, as well as Edged Weapons and Militaria we have for sale at Jackson Armory (see our other listings), this is a RZM-marked .32 caliber Walther PPK, made in 1935. As you probably know, “RZM” was the purchasing office of the Nazi Party (NOT the Whermacht, etc.) and RZM-marked guns usually went to High-Ranking Nazi Party Leaders, Gauliters, SA Officers, etc. The pistol has a factory blue finish and wrap-around plastic factory grips with the Walther banner, it also has a Walther-marked factory finger-rest magazine. Besides the RZM marking on the left side of the slide, the pistol has the correct “Crown N” proofs on the right side of the barrel and slide. The pistol is only serial-numbered on the receiver. The pistol has some holster wear on the slide, and a few service marks here and there. The factory Walther grips are in excellent condition with no cracks, however, these grips, while original, may have been replaced at some time, or, more likely, they have just shrunk over time, there is not enough clearance for the safety/de-cocker to come all the way down. Overall condition of the pistol is about 90%. The pistol has a shiny bore with strong rifling, and trigger pull is smooth. RZM PPK’s are quite desirable, this one needs a home in your collection! We do not have any accessories, extra mags, holster, etc. for this gun. * All ITEMS ONLINE ARE SUBJECT TO PRIOR SALE IN OUR RETAIL STORE
